%N A007586 11-gonal (or hendecagonal) pyramidal numbers: a(n) = n*(n+1)*(3*n-2)/2.
%C A007586 Starting with 1 equals binomial transform of [1, 11, 19, 9, 0, 0, 0, ...]. - _Gary W. Adamson_, Nov 02 2007
